title: Supercars: Freightliner Racing makes radical livery change for Tim Slade’s 2017 car | Perth Now
text:
Supercars: Freightliner Racing makes radical livery change for Tim Slade’s 2017 car Staff writers, FOX SPORTS February 17, 2017 5:00pm 
FREIGHTLINER Racing has debuted a radically changed livery on Tim Slade’s Holden for the 2017 Supercars season. 
Gone is the red. Gone is the black. In their place is a bright white and silver look with highlights of red. 
“The Freightliner Racing Commodore looks awesome,” Slade said. 
“It’s so different to what the car has been over the past few years, we’ve had the design locked down for a while now and I’m excited to finally show it off to our Freightliner Racing fans.” 
The new look is mirrored by that on the car’s new transporter, a Freightliner Coronado 114, shown off in the team’s livery reveal video below . Freightliner Racing video 
Slade broke through for his maiden Supercars race win last year, sweeping both victories at Brad Jones Racing’s home track, Winton. 
“We didn’t put too much pressure on ourselves last year, we always wanted to do well and aim for the top ten,” he added. media_camera Tim Slade’s Freightliner Racing 2017 Supercars livery. 
“We achieved some great results, and this year we’ll be looking to build on that and be more consistent with our speed and good results.” 
The new-look No. 14 Holden will the track for the first time in anger during Supercars’ tyre test day at Sydney Motorsport Park on Tuesday. media_camera
